This paper deals with visual robot self-localization, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and feature extraction, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
